Frederica Going https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederica_Going 0 Frederica Going (August 13, 1895 - April 11, 1959) was an American actress that performed in Broadway plays. Going's father is Frederick Going who was a Shakespearean actor. She performed in plays ever since she was child and has performed in multiple productions. The plays that she had performed in ranged from Shakespeare to musical comedy. Her Broadway performances include roles in Street Scene, For the Defense, Two on an Island, and A New Life which were all produced by Elmer Rice. She had a role in the 1938 educational film The Birth of a Baby. Frederica Going ( August_13_,_1895 - April_11_,_1959 ) was an_American_actress that performed in Broadway plays .
